                  <persName role="owner" corresp="PRS0000">ʿAqbä Mikaʾel is mentioned in the supplication formulas throughout the text; besides, in the conclusion of the entries for the month Miyazya, on fol. 53rc, an invocation mentions the scribe and "ʿAqbä Mikaʾel, the one who caused (the book) be written".&#xD;
In some passages, his name is replaced with the names of Śǝʿǝlä Mikaʾel (esp. fol. 157rc, l.19) and Kǝnfä Mikaʾel (esp. fol. 171ra, l.6).&#xD;
Together  with ʿAqbä Mikaʾel, "his maid Wälättä Maryam" is also mentioned (e.g., fols. 40ra, l.16, 40va, l.9, 88ra, ls. 23-24).</persName>
